     1	# ADR 0018: bounded sync and cache
     2	
     3	- Status: Accepted
     4	- Date: 2026-07-16
     5	
     6	## Context
     7	
     8	Phase 1 needs an offline recent inbox without making a lossless mailbox-sync,
     9	background-refresh, or cache-budget claim. The Gmail adapter can return an
    10	empty page with a fresh continuation token when all attempted message hydrations
    11	were 404, so bounded pagination must permit that case without risking a loop.
    12	
    13	## Decision
    14	
    15	`tersa-application::sync` owns a runtime-free recent-snapshot coordinator. A
    16	validated policy uses the existing provider `PageSize` cap of 500, a finite cap
    17	of 1,000 pages, an existing `StoreLimit` keep cap of 10,000, and a full-message
    18	cap no greater than the keep cap. The coordinator is lazy and single-flight per
    19	account; its drop-owned claim is released on cancellation, it holds no mutex
    20	guard across an await, creates no detached work, and retries nothing.
    21	
    22	It collects and validates the complete bounded snapshot before any store
    23	mutation. Pages larger than requested, repeated continuation tokens, and
    24	conflicting duplicate message identifiers fail. Exact duplicates deduplicate in
    25	provider encounter order. Collection stops at the keep limit and reports
    26	truncation. A zero-item page with a fresh token is valid.
    27	
    28	One store transaction reconciles snapshot envelopes, preserving already cached
    29	bodies and retaining only the deterministic `received_at DESC, message_id ASC`
    30	keep set. It returns only snapshot identifiers that survived, in duplicate-free
    31	provider encounter order. The coordinator fetches bodies sequentially only for
    32	those survivors and only up to the full-message cap. `NotFound` and a vanished
    33	conditional-cache row are counted as skipped; every other remote, protocol, or
    34	store failure stops immediately. The coordinator never calls general-purpose
    35	`put_message`.
    36	
    37	Reports and failures contain only counts, source categories, progress, and
    38	truncation flags. Their manual formatting does not expose identifiers, tokens,
    39	headers, or bodies.
    40	
    41	## Non-claims
    42	
    43	This is bounded recent-snapshot bootstrap/refresh only. It adds no Gmail
    44	History/cursor, deletion reconciliation, retry, background work,
    45	mutations/outbox/labels, blob/search/CLI/UI, real credentials/network tests,
    46	mobile implementation, or gate-status change. Older or deleted remote rows may
    47	remain locally until deterministic pruning displaces them. Cache budgets remain
    48	constraints, not evidence.
    49	
    50	## Consequences
    51	
    52	The local store remains responsible for atomic reconcile and conditional cache
    53	writes. Adapters continue to own their transaction and cancellation evidence;
    54	the application layer stays independent of runtimes, transports, storage
    55	engines, Apple APIs, and UI frameworks.
